'''Maj-Briht Bergström-Walan''' (7 November 1924 – 25 August 2014) was a Swedish [[psychologist]] and [[midwife]], as well as the first authorized [[sexologist]] in Sweden.<ref>[http://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=2071&artikel=2123279 Om Maj Briht Bergström-Walan], [[Sveriges Radio]] 2008-06-26 {{sv icon}}</ref><ref>[http://www.dn.se/kultur-noje/maj-briht-bergstrom-walan-dod/ Maj-Briht Bergström-Walan död], [[Dagens Nyheter]] 2014-08-27 {{sv icon}}</ref> In the 1960s and the 1970s, she was the leading personality in [[sex education]] in Sweden. On May 31, 1996 Bergström-Walan received an [[Honorary degree|honorary doctorate]] from the Faculty of Medicine at [[Uppsala University]], [[Sweden]] <ref>http://www.uu.se/en/about-uu/traditions/prizes/honorary-doctorates/</ref>

